 	

What is it?
	

HTML : A markup language used primarily for displaying structured content in a browser.
	

XML : A markup language used primarily for exchanging structured data between computer systems.

Year of release
	

HTML : 1998.
	

XML : 1993.

Purpose
	

HTML : Presentation language.
	

XML : Data exchange language.

Use when
	

HTML : Building client-side webpages or web apps.
	

XML : Exchanging data between two systems (but check if JSON is a better format for you).

Tags
	

HTML : Predefined tags.
	

XML : Extendible tags.

Typing
	

HTML : Dynamic.
	

XML : Fixed when using an XML schema.
